title: Jordan Prime Lending Rate
description: Bank Lending Rate in Jordan increased to 9.85 percent in September from 9.64 percent in August of 2022. Bank Lending Rate in Jordan averaged 8.25 percent from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 10.50 percent in March of 2000 and a record low of 6 percent in January of 2004. In Jordan, the bank lending rate represents the minimum prime lending rate for credit extended by licenced banks. This page provides - Jordan Bank Lending Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Jordan
